quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
33,36,"It<sup foot_note="180423">1</sup> does not behove a believer, male or female,"that when Allah and His Messenger have decided an affair they should exercise their choice. And whoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger has strayed to manifest error. {2}",footnotes:1:From here begin the verses which were revealed in connection with the Prophet’s (peace be upon him) marriage with Zainab (may Allah be pleased with her).|180424:Ibn Abbas
33,37,"(O Prophet), {1} call to mind when you said to him {2} whom Allah had favoured and you had favoured: “Cleave to your wife and fear Allah,” {3} and you concealed within yourself for fear of people what Allah was to reveal, although Allah has greater right that you fear Him. {4} So when Zayd had accomplished what he would of her, {5} We gave her in marriage to you {6} so that there should not be any constraint for the believers regarding the wives of their adopted sons after they had accomplished whatever they would of them. {7} And Allah's command was bound to be accomplished.",footnotes:1:These words were said when the relations between Zaid and Zainab had become very strained
33,38,"There could be no hindrance to the Prophet regarding what Allah ordained for him. {1} Such has been Allah's Way (with the Prophets) who went before. Allah's command is a decree firmly determined. {2}",footnotes:1:These words show that for the other Muslims such a marriage is just permissible but for the Prophet (peace be upon him) it was a duty which Allah had imposed on him.|180433:That is
33,39,"(This is Allah's Way) regarding those who deliver the Messages of Allah and who fear Him, and fear no one else than Allah. Allah is Sufficient as a Reckoner. {1}",footnotes:1:The words in the text have two meanings:
33,40,"Muhammad is not the father of any of your men, but he is the Messenger of Allah and the seal of the Prophets. Allah has full knowledge of everything. {1}",footnotes:1:This one sentence was at the root of all those objections which the opponents were raising in connection with this marriage of the Prophet (peace be upon him).
33,41,"Believers, remember Allah much"
33,42,"and glorify Him morning and evening. {1}",footnotes:1:This is meant to instruct the Muslims to the effect: When the Messenger (peace be upon him) of Allah is being showered with taunts and abuses by the enemies and his person being made the target of a propaganda campaign to frustrate his mission
33,43,"It is He Who lavishes His blessings on you and His angels invoke blessings on you that He may lead you out of darkness into light. He is Most Compassionate to the believers. {1}",footnotes:1:This is meant to make the Muslims realize this: The jealousy and malice of the disbelievers and hypocrites towards you is only due to the mercy that Allah has shown you through His Messenger (peace be upon him). It is through him that you have been blessed with the faith
